1
00:00:02,195 --> 00:00:07,023
Through sevā we will achieve focus.

2
00:00:07,069 --> 00:00:09,563
It has to be about sevā.

3
00:00:09,563 --> 00:00:14,331
We’re trying to serve the Holy Name,
not to have the Holy Name serve us.

4
00:00:14,380 --> 00:00:17,084
[Devotees of the Invisible]

5
00:00:17,546 --> 00:00:21,678
That’s a big difference.

6
00:00:21,940 --> 00:00:27,022
It may sound the same;
the syllables may sound the same,

7
00:00:27,089 --> 00:00:31,322
but the intention is different.

8
00:00:31,322 --> 00:00:35,495
Anyābhilāṣitā-śūnyaḿ
jñāna-karmādy-anāvṛtam;

9
00:00:35,495 --> 00:00:39,743
ulterior motive is the difference
(Brs: 1.1.11).

10
00:00:39,743 --> 00:00:42,876
We’re told—again, by
Rūpa Goswāmī (Cc 2.17.136),

11
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:47,829
“Ataḥ śrī-kṛṣṇa-nāmādi
na bhaved grāhyam indriyaiḥ.”

12
00:00:47,829 --> 00:00:51,569
The Nāma-ādi means
Nāma-rūpa-guṇa-līlā;

13
00:00:51,569 --> 00:00:56,539
the Name of Kṛṣna,
the Form of Kṛṣna,

14
00:00:56,539 --> 00:01:01,087
the Qualities of Kṛṣna,
the Pastimes of Kṛṣṇa,

15
00:01:01,087 --> 00:01:07,683
are beyond the grasp
of our mind and intellect.

16
00:01:07,683 --> 00:01:10,326
Then what?
Then what are we doing?

17
00:01:10,326 --> 00:01:15,705
Once, Guru Mahārāj said,
“We’re devotees of the invisible.”

18
00:01:15,705 --> 00:01:21,642
Everyone says, “Bunch of foolish people!
Not one of them has seen Kṛṣṇa.”

19
00:01:21,642 --> 00:01:25,945
Gurudev, even, once asked Guru Mahārāj, 
“All this talk about Kṛṣṇa-nām,

20
00:01:25,945 --> 00:01:30,992
has anyone actually got that?”

21
00:01:30,992 --> 00:01:34,942
It’s a Gurudev-type question.

22
00:01:34,942 --> 00:01:38,007
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur says,
“We were in the presence

23
00:01:38,007 --> 00:01:44,533
of Jagannāth Dās Bābājī on Ekādaśī.
He was taking Kṛṣṇ-nām,

24
00:01:44,533 --> 00:01:49,809
hair standing on end, shivering
and trembling in the body”,

25
00:01:49,809 --> 00:01:52,054
just as we’ve seen described
in the scriptures,

26
00:01:52,054 --> 00:01:55,166
described by Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur—

27
00:01:55,166 --> 00:02:02,666
that out of the sound of Kṛṣṇa-nām,
when it's real, what is the effect?

28
00:02:02,666 --> 00:02:04,693
Read what Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur says.

29
00:02:04,693 --> 00:02:09,777
You can read it in Search for Śrī Kṛṣṇa,
the chapter called Nectar of the Holy Name.

30
00:02:09,777 --> 00:02:13,959
You need to understand what it is really.

31
00:02:13,959 --> 00:02:18,048
He said, “Sometimes I’m taking Kṛṣṇa-nām

32
00:02:18,048 --> 00:02:26,727
and some mysterious form and colour
appears from the sound.

33
00:02:26,727 --> 00:02:29,257
Mysterious form: Kṛṣṇa.

34
00:02:29,257 --> 00:02:32,257
Mysterious colour: Śyāmasundar.

35
00:02:32,257 --> 00:02:35,408
Śyāmasundar Kṛṣṇa appears
out of the sound

36
00:02:35,408 --> 00:02:38,559
of Bhakti Vinoda Ṭhākur’s
Kṛṣṇa-nām.

37
00:02:38,559 --> 00:02:43,125
He said, “And then He takes me.”

38
00:02:43,448 --> 00:02:52,471
And so many other things …
and he’s describing intense ecstatic states.

39
00:02:52,471 --> 00:02:56,651
So then we’ll have to say, 
“Well that’s not our position.

40
00:02:56,651 --> 00:02:59,245
What are we doing?”

41
00:02:59,245 --> 00:03:05,947
Previously, people would say something like, 
“Oh, today I really chanted good rounds.”

42
00:03:05,947 --> 00:03:10,758
I mean I think the really good rounds
are when Kṛṣṇa comes out of the sound

43
00:03:10,758 --> 00:03:15,910
and reveals His Form and His Qualities,
and takes you into His Pastimes,

44
00:03:15,910 --> 00:03:19,396
according to Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur.

45
00:03:19,396 --> 00:03:21,245
Again, we’re saying, “What are we doing?

46
00:03:21,245 --> 00:03:24,354
We’re following the order
of Guru and Vaiṣṇava.

47
00:03:24,354 --> 00:03:28,611
You take this Kṛṣṇa-nām—Mahaprabhu also—
you take this Kṛṣṇa-nām

48
00:03:28,611 --> 00:03:35,710
under the guidance of a Vaiṣṇava, 
and engage in service and association.”

49
00:03:35,710 --> 00:03:48,979
And one day the steel frame in which
our hearts are encased will melt.

50
00:03:48,979 --> 00:03:50,717
One day.

